{"senses":[{"examples":[{"tags":["literary"],"text":"اگر سؤالی دارید، لطفا بپرسید.","bold_text_offsets":[[67,76],[109,112]],"roman":"agar so'âli dârid, lotfan be-porsid.","bold_roman_offsets":[[26,35]],"translation":"If you have a question, please ask.","english":"If you have a question, please ask.","bold_translation_offsets":[[31,34]],"type":"example"},{"tags":["colloquial"],"text":"اگه یه سؤالی دارین، لطفا بپرسین.","bold_text_offsets":[[74,83],[116,119]],"roman":"age ye so'âli dârin, lotfan bo-porsin.","bold_roman_offsets":[[28,37]],"translation":"If you have a question, please ask.","english":"If you have a question, please ask.","bold_translation_offsets":[[31,34]],"type":"example"},{"text":"از وطن پرسید و آوردش به گفت، و اندر آن پرسش بسی درها بسفت","ref":"c. 1260s, Jalāl ad-Dīn Mohammad Rūmī, translated by Reynold A. Nicholson, مثنوی معنوی [Masnavi-ye-Ma'navi], volume II, verse 3178:","english":"He asked him about his native land and led him to talk and said many fine things in the course of [his] enquiry.","roman":"az vatan porsid va âvard-eš be goft, va andar ân porseš basi dor-hâ be-soft.","type":"quotation","translation":"He asked him about his native land and led him to talk and said many fine things in the course of [his] enquiry.","bold_translation_offsets":[[3,8]]}],"links":[["ask","ask"],["inquire","inquire"]],"synonyms":[{"word":"سؤال کردن"}],"glosses":["to ask, inquire"],"categories":["Persian terms with quotations","Persian terms with usage examples"]},{"links":[["question","question"]],"glosses":["to question"]}],"pos":"verb","head_templates":[{"name":"head","args":{"1":"fa","2":"verb","sort":"","head":"","tr":"pursīdan /porsidan","3":"present stem","4":"پرس","f1tr":"purs /pors","5":"","6":"","f2tr":"","7":"","8":"","f3tr":"","9":"","f4tr":"","10":"","11":"Tajik spelling","12":"пурсидан","13":"","14":""},"expansion":"پرسیدن • (pursīdan /porsidan) (present stem پرس (purs /pors), Tajik spelling пурсидан)"},{"name":"fa-verb","args":{"1":"پُرْسِیدَن",